th largest company by revenue for  in the fortune global  list abb is one of the largest engineering companies as well as one of the largest conglomerates in the world abb has operations in around  countries with approximately  employees in december  abb is traded on the six swiss exchange in zürich nasdaq stockholm and the new york stock exchange in the united states contents  history  organizational structure  electrification products  robotics and motion  industrial automation  power grids  other  management  primary investors  see also  main competitors  references  further reading  external links historyedit see also allmänna svenska elektriska aktiebolaget and brown boveri  cie abbs history goes back to the late th century asea was founded in  by ludvig fredholm in västerås as manufacturer of electrical light and generators brown boveri  cie bbc was formed in  in baden switzerland by charles eugene lancelot brown and walter boveri as a swiss group of electrical companies producing ac and dc motors generators steam turbines and transformers abb around the worldvague abb resulted from the  merger of the swedish corporation allmänna svenska elektriska aktiebolaget asea and the swiss company brown boveri  cie bbc the latter had absorbed the maschinenfabrik oerlikon in  ceo at the time of the merger was the former ceo of asea percy barnevik who ran the company until  abb transformer in iowa being transported by the iowa interstate railroad in  abb purchased westinghouses metering and control division the load control division was spun off to cannon technologies in the late s and the meter division was spun off to elster electricity in the early s also in the early s abb purchased combustion engineering ce headquartered in stamford and norwalk connecticut a leading us firm in the development of conventional fossil fuel power and nuclear power supply systems to break into the north american market klaus agthe was ceo of the us operation at the time continuing with its expansion plans abb purchased elsag bailey a process automation group in  which included bailey controls hartmann  braun and fischer  porter this was the largest acquisition to date in abbs history abb bought international combustion ltd from rollsroyce in  abbs boiler and fossil fuel businesses were purchased by alstom in  and its nuclear business was purchased by westinghouse electric company in  in  abb also signed a contract for the delivery of equipment and services for two north korean nuclear powerplants to be supplied under an agreement with the korean peninsula energy development organization kedo a consortium formed in  by the governments of the united states japan south korea and the european union abb formally divested from a joint venture named abbalstom power in  and sold its interest in conventional power generation systems to alstom power abbs nuclear business was sold to bnfl and merged into westinghouse electric company in  abb was ranked as number one on the dow jones corporate sustainability index for the third year in a row in  abb asked lindahl the companys former chief executive to return some of his  million retirement pay which its board called excessive abb also asked its former chairman percy barnevik to pay back part of his  million pension package the size of the pensions was disclosed at the same time as abbs  million net loss for  made headlines and drew sharp criticism in switzerland and sweden abbs building systems business unit was sold off in  to capvis a swiss private equity company as part of abbs strategy to focus on power and automation technologies abbs building systems businesses in australia and hong kong were sold off the year before in may  to downer edi limited building systems provided services for building facilities encompassing indoor air quality building automation as well as power distribution and management financial debt and lingering asbestos liability brought abb to the brink of bankruptcy in the early s in  abb returned to financial health by settling its asbestos liability regarding claims that were filed against abbs us subsidiaries combustion engineering and lummus global in august  lummus global was sold to cbi in december  abb acquired bermac electrical and instrumentation to expand its presence in western canadas oil and gas industries bermac electrical and instrumentation has been in the business of supplying electrical power and instrumentation equipment and services both domestically and to international markets since  bermac provides its clients with expertise in industrial automation electrical and instrumentation design process optimization panel fabrication and field services it is particularly strong in the oil  gas industry bermac’s value proposition in engineering expertise and service capabilities is highly respected throughout western canada this was a key factor in abb’s decision to acquire the firm this acquisition significantly expanded abb’s presence in western canada to more than  employees in over  locations in  abb realigned its automation divisions to enhance growth opportunities as of january   the business units in the automation products and robotics divisions were regrouped into two new divisions – discrete automation and motion and low voltage products the process automation division remained unchanged except for the addition of the instrumentation business from the automation products division in may  abb acquired software company ventyx for more than  billion from vista equity partners in  on may  abb announced acquisition of australianbased mincom limited from private equity firm francisco partners  to expand their enterprise software business for undisclosed sum on july   acquisition has been finalised mincom and ventyx were subsequently integrated under the ventyx name and have now been integrated into abb as the enterprise software product group in  abb acquired baldor electric usa for  billion in an allcash transaction on january   abb group acquired thomas  betts in a  billion cash transaction on june   abb completed acquisition of commercial and industrial wireless technology specialists tropos in july  abb acquired powerone in a  billion allcash transaction to become the leading global manufacturer of solar inverters  organizational structureedit abb is the worlds largest builder of electricity grids and is active in many sectors its core businesses being in power and automation technologies with a long history of growth through mergers and acquisitions it entered a phase of structure unification since  the company has one corporate division and four production divisions since reorganization in january  abb is one of the few large companies that have successfully implemented the matrix structure in their organization electrification productsedit the electrification products division manufactures low and mediumvoltage electrical products including electric vehicle infrastructure solar inverters modular substations distribution automation products to protect people installations and electronic equipment from electrical overload such as enclosures cable systems and lowvoltage circuit breakers measuring and sensing devices control products switches and wiring accessories the division further makes knx systems that integrate and automate a buildings electrical installations ventilation systems and security and data communication networks electrification products also incorporates an electrification solutions unit manufacturing low voltage switchgear and motor control centres customers include a wide range of industry and utility operations plus commercial and residential buildings robotics and motionedit the robotics and motion division provides products and services for industrial production it includes electric motors generators drives power electronics and industrial robots abb has installed over  robots in  abb opened a manufacturing centre in shanghai china also wind generators solar power inverters and ups products belong to this division industrial automationedit the main focus of the industrial automation division is to provide customers with systems for control plant optimization and industryspecific automation applications the industries served include oil and gas power chemicals and pharmaceuticals pulp and paper metals and minerals marine and turbocharging the division consists of seven business units control technologies the worlds no  dcs supplier marine  ports measurement  analytics oil gas  chemicals power generation  water process industries and turbocharging power gridsedit the power grids division offers key components for the transmission and distribution of electricity the division incorporates abbs manufacturing network for transformers switchgear circuit breakers and associated high voltage equipment such as digital protective relays it also offers maintenance services the division also offers turnkey systems and service for power transmission and distribution grids and for power plants electrical substations and substation automation systems are key areas additional highlights include flexible ac transmission systems facts highvoltage direct current hvdc systems and network management systems the division is subdivided into the four business units high voltage products transformers grid automation and grid integration otheredit in may  abb sécheron sa joined with several groups in geneva tosa trolleybus optimisation système alimentation or in english trolleybus power system optimization in a oneyear demonstration of a trolleybus route using a novel charging system rather than overhead wires charging is accomplished by fixed overhead devices located at stops along the route and at the terminus jeanluc favre head of rail isi discussed the promising role of improved electric transport technology in abb managementedit ulrich spiesshofer has been chief executive officer since september  former ceos september – september  joe hogan february   september  michel demaré ad interim january   february  fred kindle september   december  jürgen dormann january   september  jörgen centerman january   december  göran lindahl  percy barnevik chairman of the board the board of directors is chaired by peter voser he was elected in april  and succeeded hubertus von grünberg who had been chairman since may  jürgen dormann was chairman from  to  and percy barnevik from  to  former board members include peter sutherland donald rumsfeld – primary investorsedit the largest single stake in the firm is held by the swedish investment company investor ab controlled by the wallenberg family which holds  see alsoedit allmänna svenska elektriska aktiebolaget eaton corporation general electric dcsps legrand nexans rockwell automation schneider electric siemens smart grid stromberg company vehicle to grid main competitorsedit alstom bharat heavy electricals ltd eaton corporation general electric havells larsen  toubro legrand nexans rockwell automation schneider electric siemens referencesedit  a b c d e abb fullyear  press release abbcom retrieved  february    a b abb annual report  pdf abbcom abb retrieved  march    fortune global  page for abb with the th rank in  fortunecom fortune   httpnewabbcominvestorrelationsshareinformationsharelisting  ludvig fredholm   walter boveri   elsag bailey was acquired by abb group  elsag bailey process automation nv was acquired by abb group wwwbloombergcom   international combustion ltd from american roots to sinfin lane bygonederbyshirecouk  retrieved    uk business park uk business park archived from the original on  january  retrieved    press release abb to deliver systems equipment to north korean nuclear plants abb  january  retrieved    randeep ramesh  the two faces of rumsfeld london the guardian   press release abb to sell nuclear business to bnfl abb  december  retrieved    dow jones sustainability indexes archived from the original on  april    edith m lederer  un swedish busi